This paper deals with evaluating the user experience of browsing web archives, which involves information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL). The study also involves human-computer interaction (HC) and web technologies (WEB). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze the web archive data, which falls under computational linguistics (CL).
